cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing a system for processing large graphs using a small cluster of machines. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as the paper discusses the challenges of out-of-core systems and the need for efficient external-memory join and group-by operations. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper introduces a vertex-centric programming interface for parallel graph algorithms. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with graph processing. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper presents extensive experiments to evaluate the performance of the proposed system.
